.SH NAME
arx-config-validate - Validate arx configuration file


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBarx config validate [path] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Validate an arx configuration file.

.PP
If no path is specified, looks for arx.yaml in the current directory.

.PP
Exit codes:
  0 - Config is valid
  1 - Config is invalid or error occurred

.PP
Examples:
  arx config validate                    # Validate arx.yaml in current dir
  arx config validate ./custom.yaml      # Validate specific file
  arx config validate --path ./arx.yaml  # Using --path flag


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for validate

.PP
\fB-p\fP, \fB--path\fP=""
	Path to config file (default: arx.yaml)


